WEBVTT

1
00:02:29.335 --> 00:02:32.133
<i>- Sí. Bueno.
- Family is everything.</i>

2
00:02:32.238 --> 00:02:34.035
<i>No?</i>

3
00:02:34.140 --> 00:02:37.542
<i>Now. do you love your son?</i>

4
00:02:38.512 --> 00:02:42.278
Sí.

5
00:02:49.156 --> 00:02:53.753
<i>Now... do you understand?</i>

6
00:02:53.861 --> 00:02:58.230
<i>You have a $10 million insurance policy.
I know that.</i>

7
00:05:07.736 --> 00:05:09.863
Georgina!

8
00:05:09.971 --> 00:05:13.236
Obey me. I will love you.
Come on.

9
00:05:13.341 --> 00:05:15.104
That's how it works. huh?

10
00:05:15.210 --> 00:05:18.374
<i>- Simple.
- That's right.</i>

11
00:05:18.481 --> 00:05:20.381
Mwah.

12
00:05:24.520 --> 00:05:27.819
She got a sister?

13
00:05:27.923 --> 00:05:31.120
How's business?

14
00:05:31.227 --> 00:05:34.128
The Japanese are here in a big way.

15
00:05:35.564 --> 00:05:38.056
Cheap labor. factory space.

16
00:05:38.168 --> 00:05:42.127
But they feel a lot safer living
over the border in El Paso.

17
00:05:42.239 --> 00:05:45.299
I ferry them back and forth.
They think I'm John Wayne.

18
00:05:45.409 --> 00:05:47.309
- Ah.
- Come on.

19
00:05:51.782 --> 00:05:55.014
- I live like a king down here.
- Yes. you do.

20
00:05:58.756 --> 00:06:01.919
- You been workin'?
- Yeah. No.

21
00:06:02.026 --> 00:06:04.085
Nah. Been movin' around.
you know.

22
00:06:04.195 --> 00:06:08.256
Colombia. couple of places I can't name.
Nothing catches my fancy.

23
00:06:10.134 --> 00:06:13.104
Oh.

24
00:06:13.205 --> 00:06:15.765
You think God will forgive us
for what we've done?

25
00:06:15.874 --> 00:06:18.434
- No.
- You don't?

26
00:06:18.544 --> 00:06:22.708
Me either.

27
00:06:22.815 --> 00:06:27.616
- How long you staying?
- I don't know. I just... you know.

28
00:06:27.719 --> 00:06:31.679
I wanted to see you. Ray.
see how you're doin'.

29
00:06:31.791 --> 00:06:34.316
You know. I came by on impulse.

30
00:06:34.427 --> 00:06:37.988
Well. I could do with some impulse.

31
00:06:48.107 --> 00:06:51.134
What happened?

32
00:06:51.245 --> 00:06:53.440
Family paid the ransom...

33
00:06:53.547 --> 00:06:57.540
then they sent the kid home
after a couple of days...

34
00:06:57.651 --> 00:06:59.812
minus an ear. of course.

35
00:06:59.920 --> 00:07:03.549
Now every mother in Mexico City with a little
bit of money wants bigger and better bodyguards...

36
00:07:03.657 --> 00:07:05.625
my own wife included.

37
00:07:05.726 --> 00:07:09.026
I hate to break it to you.
but she's right. She's right.

38
00:07:10.732 --> 00:07:14.998
Look. Sammy. all my clients have. uh.
kidnap and ransom insurance.

39
00:07:15.103 --> 00:07:18.334
I have a policy. A.I.G.
My dad gave it to me.

40
00:07:18.440 --> 00:07:21.705
Yeah. I know.
I got it for your dad.

41
00:07:21.810 --> 00:07:24.745
<i>But what are you gonna do in 60 days
when you can't renew it?</i>

42
00:07:24.847 --> 00:07:29.113
- You can't because you don't have a bodyguard.
- I had to let Emilio go.

43
00:07:29.218 --> 00:07:32.847
You gotta please Lisa.
I mean. hey. ass like that's hard to find.

44
00:07:35.291 --> 00:07:39.557
Look. a bodyguard's
like anything else.

45
00:07:39.662 --> 00:07:42.928
You get what you pay for. okay?

46
00:07:43.033 --> 00:07:46.025
You could do this.
You get one that's got a decent résumé.

47
00:07:46.136 --> 00:07:48.468
We're not looking for
goddamn Superman here. right?

48
00:07:48.572 --> 00:07:51.302
Get someone cheap
till you renew the policy...

49
00:07:51.408 --> 00:07:54.775
and then. uh...
then fire the prick for whatever.

50
00:07:54.878 --> 00:07:56.937
Incompetence.

51
00:07:57.047 --> 00:08:01.451
All kidding aside. the most important thing
is that your daughter goes back to school...

52
00:08:01.553 --> 00:08:04.522
and that your wife gets to save face.

53
00:08:04.622 --> 00:08:09.423
This way. you won't be the only
unprotected family in the neighborhood.

54
00:08:22.041 --> 00:08:25.238
<i>That's right. A bodyguard.
Your Spanish is good enough.</i>

55
00:08:25.344 --> 00:08:28.745
- You're crazy.
- You even look the part.

56
00:08:28.847 --> 00:08:31.315
In my state.
I couldn't guard a corpse.

57
00:08:31.417 --> 00:08:34.215
<i>It's rich guys flashing their cash.
It's all for show.</i>

58
00:08:34.320 --> 00:08:39.452
<i>- Nothing's gonna happen. - Yeah? You
think they'd hire a drunk. a has-been?</i>

59
00:08:41.127 --> 00:08:44.426
You have to keep it under control.

60
00:08:44.531 --> 00:08:49.298
What if there was. you know. say.
a kidnapping attempt? What do I do then?

61
00:08:49.402 --> 00:08:53.429
<i>You do your best. They're not gonna be
paying you enough to perform miracles.</i>

62
00:08:53.540 --> 00:08:56.135
<i>- I don't know.
- It's not exactly a scam. Crease.</i>

63
00:08:56.243 --> 00:09:00.475
- Even at half speed. you're pretty damn good.
- Yeah.

64
00:09:00.581 --> 00:09:02.776
Bodyguard's gotta be close
to people though.

65
00:09:02.883 --> 00:09:05.716
He gotta talk all the time.
and I'm no good at that.

66
00:09:05.820 --> 00:09:09.347
You'll be the silent type.
People are gonna appreciate that.

67
00:09:16.298 --> 00:09:19.165
Bodyguard. So who's the guy?

68
00:09:19.267 --> 00:09:22.168
Samuel Ramos. He's a young guy.

69
00:09:22.270 --> 00:09:25.068
<i>He owns one of the plants in Juárez.</i>

70
00:09:25.173 --> 00:09:27.107
<i>Yeah?</i>

71
00:09:27.209 --> 00:09:30.007
The Jap car industry is in the toilet.

72
00:09:30.112 --> 00:09:33.048
He's trying to persuade Ford
to partner with him.

73
00:09:33.149 --> 00:09:37.017
I think he's in trouble.
His family lives in Mexico City.

74
00:09:37.120 --> 00:09:39.645
He asked me if I knew
anybody he could trust.

75
00:09:41.224 --> 00:09:44.216
- And you thought of me.
- Yeah.

76
00:09:44.327 --> 00:09:47.728
Take a job. Crease.
Breathe some air.

77
00:09:47.830 --> 00:09:50.197
<i>Then decide if you want
to stick around or not.</i>

78
00:09:50.300 --> 00:09:54.396
<i>Besides. I'm glad to see you.
I got nobody to talk to down here.</i>

79
00:10:01.879 --> 00:10:04.780
Listen. my wife wants someone
presentable and polite.

80
00:10:07.151 --> 00:10:10.679
You'll be the fifth candidate
she sees this week.

81
00:10:10.789 --> 00:10:12.518
Your résumé's quite impressive.

82
00:10:12.624 --> 00:10:17.084
<i>Sixteen years of military experience.
extensive counterterrorism work.</i>

83
00:10:17.195 --> 00:10:20.756
I'm surprised anybody could afford you.
What's the catch?

84
00:10:20.865 --> 00:10:23.129
I drink.

85
00:10:23.234 --> 00:10:25.225
How does that affect you?

86
00:10:25.336 --> 00:10:27.805
Well...

87
00:10:27.907 --> 00:10:30.034
coordination. reaction time.

88
00:10:30.142 --> 00:10:33.908
If top professionals try to kidnap
your daughter. I'll do the best I can...

89
00:10:34.013 --> 00:10:37.039
but the service will be
on par with the pay.

90
00:10:38.184 --> 00:10:40.209
What if amateurs tried?

91
00:10:40.319 --> 00:10:43.447
I'd probably kill 'em.
Is that likely?

92
00:10:43.556 --> 00:10:45.525
No.

93
00:10:45.625 --> 00:10:48.389
No one is to know about your drinking.
That includes my wife.

94
00:11:15.289 --> 00:11:18.053
<i>Lisa!</i>

95
00:11:20.262 --> 00:11:22.162
Lisa!

96
00:11:33.375 --> 00:11:36.276
My wife. Lisa.
And this is John Creasy.

97
00:11:43.319 --> 00:11:45.549
- You're an American.
- So are you.

98
00:11:47.590 --> 00:11:49.387
It's all in there.

99
00:11:52.428 --> 00:11:54.362
Would you like a drink?

100
00:11:54.464 --> 00:11:57.195
Yes. uh. Jack and water'd be good.

101
00:11:58.769 --> 00:12:02.296
<i>- Have you done much of this kind of work before?
- No. ma'am.</i>

102
00:12:02.406 --> 00:12:06.172
But he has a lot of experience
in related fields.

103
00:12:08.679 --> 00:12:11.375
- You have a family. Mr. Creasy?
- No.

104
00:12:11.482 --> 00:12:13.677
Pita.

105
00:12:13.784 --> 00:12:15.753
<i>Pita.</i>

106
00:12:17.088 --> 00:12:19.181
<i>- Thank you.
- Yes. Mom?</i>

107
00:12:19.291 --> 00:12:21.191
Honey. this is. uh. Mr. Creasy.

108
00:12:26.364 --> 00:12:28.832
In English. honey.

109
00:12:28.934 --> 00:12:31.562
Um. do you wanna show
Mr. Creasy to his room?

110
00:12:31.670 --> 00:12:35.368
- This way. Mr. Creasy.
- Okay.

111
00:12:43.382 --> 00:12:45.782
Thank you.

112
00:12:52.726 --> 00:12:55.524
Just like that?

113
00:12:55.629 --> 00:12:58.029
I think it's nice...

114
00:12:58.131 --> 00:13:00.599
that he's an American.

115
00:13:00.701 --> 00:13:04.899
I think it's terrific. You sure?

116
00:13:07.574 --> 00:13:09.873
Thank you.

117
00:13:09.978 --> 00:13:12.606
Thank you.

118
00:13:12.714 --> 00:13:15.182
I feel better now.

119
00:13:17.085 --> 00:13:19.986
<i>- ¡Hola. Bruno!
- ¡Buenas tardes!</i>

120
00:13:20.088 --> 00:13:22.386
That's Bruno. the gardener.

121
00:13:22.490 --> 00:13:24.549
And. um. that's Maria. the cook.

122
00:13:24.659 --> 00:13:27.458
<i>- ¡Hola. Maria!
- Hola. Pita.</i>

123
00:13:29.732 --> 00:13:33.759
We fixed the room up two weeks ago.
It's nicer than before.

124
00:13:36.939 --> 00:13:40.773
<i>You've got a TV and C.D. Player.
What kind of music do you like. Mr. Creasy?</i>

125
00:13:40.876 --> 00:13:43.242
I don't know.

126
00:13:43.345 --> 00:13:45.837
- You don't know?
- I don't know.

127
00:13:45.949 --> 00:13:49.112
That's Bird.

128
00:13:49.219 --> 00:13:52.086
Emilio forgot to take him
when he left.

129
00:13:53.256 --> 00:13:55.588
Emilio was my last bodyguard.

130
00:13:57.594 --> 00:14:01.826
Have you protected a lot of children
before. Mr. Creasy?

131
00:14:01.932 --> 00:14:04.697
Creasy. You can call me Creasy.
And no. you're the first.

132
00:14:04.802 --> 00:14:06.702
Creasy.

133
00:14:06.804 --> 00:14:08.738
Bye. Creasy.

134
00:14:08.839 --> 00:14:11.501
So long.

135
00:14:12.610 --> 00:14:14.339
Bye. Bird.

136
00:14:19.016 --> 00:14:21.349
Ow.

137
00:14:24.323 --> 00:14:27.815
- School tomorrow. peeps.
- Does that mean we can get a dog?

138
00:14:29.227 --> 00:14:31.695
<i>Dad promised me one
when I went back to school.</i>

139
00:14:31.797 --> 00:14:33.492
Yeah. we'll see.

140
00:14:33.598 --> 00:14:37.398
If you get a dog.
will you give up your bear?

141
00:14:37.502 --> 00:14:40.836
You're getting too old for him.

142
00:14:40.940 --> 00:14:44.341
<i>- How'd you like Mr. Creasy?
- Creasy.</i>

143
00:14:44.444 --> 00:14:46.810
He said to call him just Creasy.

144
00:14:46.913 --> 00:14:49.381
- Uh-huh.
- That isn't disrespectful. is it?

145
00:14:49.482 --> 00:14:51.780
No. not if he asked you.

146
00:14:51.884 --> 00:14:54.717
Here. There you go.

147
00:15:02.563 --> 00:15:06.363
- He's like a bear too.
- Yeah?

148
00:15:06.467 --> 00:15:08.765
A big. sad bear.

149
00:15:10.404 --> 00:15:14.033
- Is he sad?
- I think. Or something.

150
00:15:17.846 --> 00:15:19.746
- Good night. honey.
- Night.

151
00:15:23.184 --> 00:15:26.449
- Oh. can you get me some floss in the morning?
- Floss?

152
00:15:26.554 --> 00:15:30.081
- Yeah. the strawberry kind.
- Oh. sure.

153
00:15:32.427 --> 00:15:34.453
Good night. Bear.

154
00:15:35.564 --> 00:15:37.532
Creasy Bear.

155
00:16:11.069 --> 00:16:13.401
What's that one for?

156
00:16:13.504 --> 00:16:15.404
<i>La Virgin de Guadalupe.</i>

157
00:16:15.506 --> 00:16:19.909
Business. For Toyota. for Ford.

158
00:16:20.011 --> 00:16:22.639
If one dies. maybe she can
resurrect the other one.

159
00:16:22.747 --> 00:16:25.307
I don't know.

160
00:16:25.416 --> 00:16:28.352
She likes him.

161
00:16:30.055 --> 00:16:33.252
- What are you talking about?
- Creasy.

162
00:16:34.793 --> 00:16:37.455
Pita likes him.

163
00:16:37.563 --> 00:16:39.463
Pita loves school.

164
00:16:39.565 --> 00:16:44.764
<i>Pita would love Count Dracula
if he took her back there. honey.</i>

165
00:16:44.870 --> 00:16:46.839
Okay?

166
00:16:49.309 --> 00:16:52.176
<i>- Hey. Are you okay?
- I don't know.</i>

167
00:16:52.278 --> 00:16:56.374
Okay?

168
00:16:56.483 --> 00:16:58.917
I don't know. Lisa.

169
00:16:59.018 --> 00:17:00.986
I'm trying.

170
00:17:56.179 --> 00:17:58.148
Come on. Bird.

171
00:17:58.248 --> 00:18:01.615
That's right.
That's right. Come on.

172
00:18:01.718 --> 00:18:04.881
All right. Home to Emilio.

173
00:18:04.988 --> 00:18:07.855
You're home free. baby.

174
00:18:27.979 --> 00:18:30.743
- Where are you from. Creasy?
- The U.S.

175
00:18:30.848 --> 00:18:33.784
<i>- I know. but which state?
- No state in particular.</i>

176
00:18:33.886 --> 00:18:35.877
You can drive and talk
at the same time.

177
00:18:35.988 --> 00:18:38.456
No. I can't. Pita. so. please.
let me just do my job.

178
00:18:41.760 --> 00:18:44.627
Are you going to stay?

179
00:18:44.730 --> 00:18:46.630
My last bodyguard left.

180
00:18:46.732 --> 00:18:49.599
Somebody gave him
more money than we could.

181
00:18:49.702 --> 00:18:53.662
I guess that makes me
a bargain then. huh?

182
00:18:53.773 --> 00:18:58.176
Being black... is that a positive or negative
for a bodyguard in Mexico?

183
00:18:58.278 --> 00:19:00.178
Time will tell.

184
00:19:03.717 --> 00:19:07.949
There were 24 kidnappings
in Mexico City in the last six days.

185
00:19:08.054 --> 00:19:09.955
- Four a day.
- Yeah?

186
00:19:10.057 --> 00:19:12.525
- Twenty-four? - Twenty-four. What
do you think about that. Creasy?

187
00:19:12.627 --> 00:19:16.290
- I think that you know entirely more than you should.
- Well. thank you.

188
00:19:39.421 --> 00:19:42.049
<i>Hola. Miguel.</i>

189
00:19:44.593 --> 00:19:46.459
- See you later.
- You have to sign.

190
00:19:46.562 --> 00:19:50.862
- What?
- You have to sign in. show them your I.D.

191
00:19:50.967 --> 00:19:54.403
<i>Buenos días. Come on.</i>

192
00:19:55.571 --> 00:19:57.471
Right there.

193
00:19:57.573 --> 00:20:00.201
<i>- Hola. Manuel.
- Hola. Pita.</i>

194
00:20:10.988 --> 00:20:12.888
<i>- ¡Hola. Pita!
- ¡Hola!</i>

195
00:20:12.990 --> 00:20:17.188
Pita! It's so good to have you back.

196
00:20:17.294 --> 00:20:20.195
Sister Anna. this is
my new bodyguard. Creasy.

197
00:20:20.297 --> 00:20:23.426
Sister Anna. the headmistress.

198
00:20:23.535 --> 00:20:25.560
<i>Señor Creasy.</i>

199
00:20:25.670 --> 00:20:27.570
Hurry. Class is about to begin.

200
00:20:27.672 --> 00:20:30.004
- Go. go.
- Bye. Creasy.

201
00:20:30.108 --> 00:20:32.599
<i>- Madre.
- You must look after our Pita.</i>

202
00:20:32.711 --> 00:20:34.906
It is not good that she's late today.

203
00:20:35.013 --> 00:20:39.575
I'm very sorry. I. uh... I'll have to get
used to the rules. It won't happen again.

204
00:20:39.684 --> 00:20:43.246
No offense. but I regret
that your profession needs to exist.

205
00:20:43.356 --> 00:20:46.484
<i>So do I. Madre. So do I.</i>

206
00:20:46.592 --> 00:20:50.551
Do you ever see the hand of God
in what you do?

207
00:20:52.164 --> 00:20:54.291
No. not for a long time.

208
00:20:54.400 --> 00:20:57.767
The Bible says.
"Be not overcome of evil. but overcome... "

209
00:20:57.870 --> 00:21:01.307
"Overcome evil with good. "

210
00:21:07.447 --> 00:21:10.245
<i>I'm the sheep that got lost. Madre.</i>

211
00:22:13.651 --> 00:22:16.711
When you were a kid. Creasy.
did you like school?

212
00:22:18.289 --> 00:22:20.484
- I don't remember.
- You don't remember?

213
00:22:20.591 --> 00:22:24.493
No. I don't remember.
It. uh... Nah. I didn't like it.

214
00:22:24.595 --> 00:22:26.654
Why not?

215
00:22:26.764 --> 00:22:29.325
Because it wasn't a school like yours.

216
00:22:29.434 --> 00:22:31.402
There was no. uh... no Sister Anna.

217
00:22:34.306 --> 00:22:36.433
Were you unhappy?

218
00:22:38.643 --> 00:22:42.044
Being unhappy. Pita. that's a state of mind.
I really don't remember.

219
00:22:51.491 --> 00:22:53.584
What happened to your hand?

220
00:22:55.127 --> 00:22:57.027
- It's a birth defect.
- No. it's not.

221
00:22:57.129 --> 00:23:01.395
Look. no more questions. okay?

222
00:23:01.501 --> 00:23:03.867
- It really wasn't a question.
- It sounded like a question.

223
00:23:03.970 --> 00:23:06.565
<i>Look. I got a job to do. Hey!</i>

224
00:23:06.673 --> 00:23:08.903
<i>No. Gracias. Gracias. No. No.</i>

225
00:23:09.009 --> 00:23:11.944
Listen to me.
I'm being paid to protect you. okay?

226
00:23:12.045 --> 00:23:15.014
No. no. no. I'm being paid
to be your bodyguard.

227
00:23:15.115 --> 00:23:18.209
<i>Look at me.
I'm not being paid to be your friend.</i>

228
00:23:18.318 --> 00:23:21.879
<i>I'm being paid to protect you.
so no more questions. That's it. Period.</i>

229
00:23:25.693 --> 00:23:28.389
<i>- You hear me?
- Yes.</i>

230
00:23:28.496 --> 00:23:31.932
- And no crying.
- I'm not crying.

231
00:23:32.033 --> 00:23:35.093
Well. don't start.

232
00:23:35.203 --> 00:23:37.637
You gotta understand. this is a job.

233
00:23:37.739 --> 00:23:40.537
In order for me to do...

234
00:23:40.642 --> 00:23:42.577
In order for... Wait a minute.

235
00:24:32.229 --> 00:24:34.197
Yeah. come in.

236
00:24:39.805 --> 00:24:41.966
Mr. Creasy.

237
00:24:42.074 --> 00:24:44.872
I just wanted to make sure
you have everything you need.

238
00:24:44.977 --> 00:24:46.945
I'm fine. thanks.

239
00:24:49.047 --> 00:24:52.380
