- Okay.

324
00:35:30.758 --> 00:35:33.693
- I love you.
- Love you.

325
00:35:33.794 --> 00:35:35.762
<i>- Okay. Bye. honey.
- Señora.</i>

326
00:35:35.863 --> 00:35:37.956
<i>- Bye.
- Oh. Gracias.</i>

327
00:35:38.065 --> 00:35:40.533
<i>- Okay. Bye. honey!
- Bye.</i>

328
00:35:40.634 --> 00:35:42.932
- I love you.
- Love you.

329
00:35:46.608 --> 00:35:49.304
I hate leaving her.

330
00:36:03.125 --> 00:36:05.252
Concentratin'?

331
00:36:05.361 --> 00:36:07.591
Eyes are closed?

332
00:36:10.333 --> 00:36:12.301
What happened?

333
00:36:12.401 --> 00:36:14.926
- I flinched.
- You flinched? The gunshot holds no fear.

334
00:36:15.037 --> 00:36:16.834
- Say it.
- The gunshot holds no fear.

335
00:36:16.939 --> 00:36:19.373
The gunshot holds no fear! Say it.

336
00:36:19.475 --> 00:36:21.444
- The gunshot holds no fear.
- Louder!

337
00:36:21.545 --> 00:36:23.513
- The gunshot holds no fear!
- Louder!

338
00:36:23.613 --> 00:36:25.837
- The gunshot holds no fear!
- That's good.

339
00:36:25.949 --> 00:36:27.940
You welcome the sound.

340
00:36:28.051 --> 00:36:30.349
In fact. it's the sound
that sets you free.

341
00:36:30.454 --> 00:36:33.389
You are a prisoner on this block
until that sound sets you free.

342
00:36:33.490 --> 00:36:35.856
- Are you ready? Are you ready?
- Yes. Yes.

343
00:36:35.959 --> 00:36:37.551
- Are you set?
- Uh-huh.

344
00:36:44.836 --> 00:36:46.804
- Creasy?
- Hmm?

345
00:36:46.904 --> 00:36:50.067
- What's a concubine?
- Why do you ask?

346
00:36:50.174 --> 00:36:52.574
It's in my history book.

347
00:36:52.677 --> 00:36:55.407
- Oh.
- It's like a wife. right?

348
00:36:55.513 --> 00:36:58.813
Yeah. Yes. uh... Can I see that?

349
00:36:58.917 --> 00:37:01.442
- Kind of a wife.
- Right there.

350
00:37:01.553 --> 00:37:04.681
But the emperor of China
had 1.000 of them.

351
00:37:04.790 --> 00:37:06.724
Um...

352
00:37:06.825 --> 00:37:10.921
Okay. like nowadays in-in the West.
they have one husband for one wife.

353
00:37:11.029 --> 00:37:13.589
But in the olden time cultures.
they had. uh...

354
00:37:13.699 --> 00:37:17.295
you know. different...
uh. different rules.

355
00:37:19.172 --> 00:37:21.936
- Why. you feel sorry for the husband?
- Yeah.

356
00:37:22.041 --> 00:37:24.441
Can you imagine my mom
multiplied by a thousand?

357
