01:17:44.923 --> 01:17:48.154
That's C-5-T-K-8.

715
01:17:48.259 --> 01:17:51.490
I got everything but the last digit.
so I need 10 possible matches.

716
01:17:51.596 --> 01:17:54.724
And when do I find out
which of the 10 it is?

717
01:17:54.833 --> 01:17:57.564
- Eventually.
- Well. where do I reach you?

718
01:17:57.670 --> 01:18:01.333
I'll call you.

719
01:18:19.159 --> 01:18:22.128
Jordan. Angola. Lebanon.
Yes. I know all of that.

720
01:18:22.229 --> 01:18:27.531
He's an assassin. And you want to help him
identify the owner of a car for him?

721
01:18:37.712 --> 01:18:40.408
<i>- Mariana.
- Sí.</i>

722
01:18:49.457 --> 01:18:51.790
<i>Gracias.</i>

723
01:18:53.395 --> 01:18:55.295
Ciao.

724
01:19:28.866 --> 01:19:31.664
Now. Jorge Gonzales.

725
01:19:38.876 --> 01:19:40.901
Okay.

726
01:20:06.272 --> 01:20:08.740
<i>What are you gonna do?
What are you gonna do?</i>

727
01:20:08.841 --> 01:20:10.809
<i>What I do best.</i>

728
01:20:12.578 --> 01:20:15.046
<i>Anyone who was involved.
Anybody who profited from it.</i>

729
01:20:15.148 --> 01:20:17.708
<i>Anybody who opens their eyes at me.
I'm gonna kill 'em.</i>

730
01:20:29.163 --> 01:20:31.222
Oh. God!

731
01:20:59.995 --> 01:21:02.486
<i>"Oye Como Va. "</i>

732
01:21:25.155 --> 01:21:27.123
Hey. hey. hey. hey. hey.

733
01:21:34.265 --> 01:21:36.165
<i>Okay? Ahora.</i>

734
01:21:40.037 --> 01:21:42.232
Huh? You know who I am?

735
01:21:49.714 --> 01:21:51.740
Correct.

736
01:21:51.850 --> 01:21:53.545
Okay.

737
01:21:53.652 --> 01:21:55.882
Hey. hey. hey.

738
01:22:38.299 --> 01:22:40.164
<i>No sé nada.</i>

739
01:22:58.386 --> 01:23:01.048
<i>¡No sé! ¡No sé!</i>

740
01:23:20.609 --> 01:23:22.237
<i>Hmm?</i>

741
01:23:30.020 --> 01:23:32.887
<i>La Voice.</i>

742
01:23:52.276 --> 01:23:54.767
Okay.

743
01:23:54.879 --> 01:23:58.179
Okay.

744
01:25:14.864 --> 01:25:17.526
Okay. Well.

745
01:25:17.633 --> 01:25:19.692
<i>Wait. wait. wait.</i>

746
01:25:19.802 --> 01:25:23.101
Give me one cigarette. please.

747
01:25:23.206 --> 01:25:25.674
<i>- Sí.
- Okay.</i>

748
01:25:30.814 --> 01:25:33.112
<i>¿Bueno?</i>

749
01:25:35.052 --> 01:25:39.682
Okay. my friend.
It's off to the next life for you.

750
01:25:41.191 --> 01:25:44.627
I guarantee you.
you won't be lonely.

751
01:26:08.888 --> 01:26:12.415
<i>Revenge is a meal best served cold.</i>

752
01:27:51.729 --> 01:27:53.823
<i>- La niña.
- No.</i>

753
01:27:53.932 --> 01:27:56.162
<i>¿No? Vamos.</i>

754
01:28:59.334 --> 01:29:01.325
No?

755
01:29:04.205 --> 01:29:06.037
Hmm?

756
01:29:17.119 --> 01:29:20.418
I heard you speaking Spanish.
You're American. right?

757
01:29:20.522 --> 01:29:22.387
- And so are you.
- Yeah.

758
01:29:22.491 --> 01:29:24.960
- Get out of here. Where are you from?
- I'm from New Jersey.

759
01:29:25.061 --> 01:29:26.426
<i>- You from New Jersey?
- Yeah.</i>

760
01:29:26.529 --> 01:29:28.759
I'm from New Jersey.
All right. listen to me.

761
01:29:32.102 --> 01:29:34.730
<i>All right. Everything
is done up by cell phone.</i>

762
01:29:34.838 --> 01:29:38.103
You just wait around for calls.
and we don't even have a fucking number.

763
01:29:38.208 --> 01:29:40.233
Who pays you?

764
01:29:40.343 --> 01:29:45.407
We got an A.T.M. Card. We take out 200
fucking measly dollars every two weeks.

765
01:29:47.151 --> 01:29:49.085
- Two hundred dollars?
- Yeah.

766
01:29:49.186 --> 01:29:51.484
- What's the PI N number?
- The what?

767
01:29:51.589 --> 01:29:53.420
The PI N number.
Code number.

768
01:29:57.194 --> 01:29:59.459
- Yeah.
- Good. You wouldn't lie to me. right?

769
01:29:59.564 --> 01:30:01.964
- I'm not lying. man.
- Did you kill her? You didn't kill her. did you?

770
01:30:02.067 --> 01:30:04.092
No.

771
01:30:06.238 --> 01:30:09.173
Don't lie to me. Don't lie to me!
Did you kill her?

772
01:30:09.274 --> 01:30:11.003
Oh. man. you're making me
fucking nervous.

773
01:30:11.109 --> 01:30:14.010
- Did you kill her?
- No way. The fucking boss did. or his brother.

774
01:30:16.748 --> 01:30:19.445
- We never see his face.
- You're not lying to me. are you?

775
01:30:19.552 --> 01:30:21.782
No. Goddamn it! I'm telling you the truth!

776
01:30:21.888 --> 01:30:24.413
Tell me. who?
You never see whose face?

777
01:30:24.524 --> 01:30:26.856
<i>Well. we were in the other room...</i>

778
01:30:26.959 --> 01:30:30.190
<i>and he was yellin' at the girl
'cause his nephew got killed...</i>

779
01:30:30.296 --> 01:30:32.696
<i>and the money got stolen.</i>

780
01:30:32.799 --> 01:30:34.699
Wait. wait. Wh-What?
Somebody stole what money?

781
01:30:34.801 --> 01:30:37.600
- The ransom money at the drop.
- Who? Who stole it?

782
01:30:37.704 --> 01:30:40.104
- He said some fuckin' crooked cop took it.
- Who?

783
01:30:40.207 --> 01:30:42.368
- Fuentes.
- Fuentes?

784
01:30:42.476 --> 01:30:44.535
<i>Yeah. that's right.</i>

785
01:30:44.645 --> 01:30:47.273
<i>All right? Huh? Jersey boy?</i>

786
01:30:47.381 --> 01:30:51.283
Yeah. Now.

787
01:30:52.553 --> 01:30:55.216
<i>- This Fuentes guy?
- Yeah.</i>

788
01:30:55.323 --> 01:30:57.723
<i>He's a lieutenant for
the Anti-Kidnapping Division.</i>

789
01:30:57.826 --> 01:31:00.317
Fuentes is. What'd you do?

790
01:31:00.428 --> 01:31:02.988
- Oh. man.
- Tell me about the girl. What'd you do?

791
01:31:03.097 --> 01:31:05.657
<i>- Huh? What'd you do?
- I just do what they told me.</i>

792
01:31:05.767 --> 01:31:07.166
- You do what they tell you to do?
- Yeah.

793
01:31:07.268 --> 01:31:09.736
Did you say good-bye to her?
Answer my question.

794
01:31:09.838 --> 01:31:11.830
- Did you say good-bye to her?
- No!

795
01:31:11.941 --> 01:31:14.409
- You didn't? Here's your chance. Say good-bye.
- Oh. shit!

796
01:31:14.510 --> 01:31:17.240
Say good-bye to her.
Say good-bye to her.

797
01:31:17.346 --> 01:31:19.473
Fucking let me go!

798
01:31:22.117 --> 01:31:24.483
Rico?

799
01:32:05.664 --> 01:32:07.564
Okay. Okay.

800
01:32:24.517 --> 01:32:26.041
<i>- No?
- No.</i>

801
01:32:43.704 --> 01:32:45.535
<i>Sí.</i>

802
01:32:48.242 --> 01:32:50.506
<i>Sí.</i>

803
01:34:25.644 --> 01:34:27.771
<i>- Sí. Guerrero.
- Listen. it's me.</i>

804
01:34:27.880 --> 01:34:30.975
Yeah. it's me. You know anything about
a young girl being kidnapped recently?

805
01:34:31.084 --> 01:34:34.247
- She's about 12 years old?
- Yes. that's last night.

806
01:34:34.354 --> 01:34:36.083
- Do you know something?
- What's her name?

807
01:34:36.189 --> 01:34:38.180
Uh. Camilla. Camilla Valencias.

808
01:34:38.291 --> 01:34:41.590
<i>¿Camilla?
¿Se llama Camilla?</i>

809
01:34:41.695 --> 01:34:43.526
<i>- Sí.
- Okay. I got her.</i>

810
01:34:43.630 --> 01:34:46.360
Where are you?

811
01:35:16.098 --> 01:35:18.896
<i>- Creasy. what happened?
- It's okay.</i>

812
01:35:19.000 --> 01:35:20.968
Sit down. Relax.

813
01:35:21.069 --> 01:35:23.902
She's okay. She's okay.
You got banking connections?

814
01:35:24.005 --> 01:35:27.407
Yes. I have connections.

815
01:35:29.112 --> 01:35:32.343
Okay. The PI N number's 4747.

816
01:35:32.448 --> 01:35:35.940
I wanna find out who's
putting money in that account.

817
01:35:36.052 --> 01:35:39.613
4747.

818
01:35:39.722 --> 01:35:42.156
What do you know
about a cop named Fuentes?

819
01:35:42.259 --> 01:35:44.489
He's with the Anti-Kidnapping Division.

820
01:35:44.595 --> 01:35:46.995
<i>He's the one who drove
Samuel Ramos to the drop.</i>

821
01:35:47.097 --> 01:35:48.689
- Fuentes?
- Sí.

822
01:35:48.799 --> 01:35:52.792
<i>- Who is she?
- You can ask her later. She'll tell you anything.</i>

823
01:35:52.903 --> 01:35:55.701
- What do you know about him?
About Fuentes?

824
01:35:55.806 --> 01:35:59.207
Three years ago they caught him with $50.000
and a dead body in the trunk of his car.

825
01:35:59.309 --> 01:36:01.005
<i>- Huh.
- Never charged.</i>

826
01:36:01.112 --> 01:36:03.979
Arresting officer couldn't testify
'cause he was dead.

827
01:36:05.583 --> 01:36:07.983
<i>- Is he La Hermandad?
- Mm-hmm.</i>

828
01:36:08.086 --> 01:36:11.613
- You know where he lives?
- He lives in a judicial compound.

829
01:36:13.558 --> 01:36:16.459
He travels by motorcade.

830
01:36:19.832 --> 01:36:22.198
<i>Creasy. he's better protected
than the president of Mexico.</i>

831
01:36:22.301 --> 01:36:24.565
He's gonna need it.
You gonna take care of her?

832
01:36:24.670 --> 01:36:27.195
- Yes. Well. how can I find you?
- I'll find you.

833
01:36:54.969 --> 01:36:58.905
This is my jurisdiction.

834
01:36:59.006 --> 01:37:03.409
I want this man as much as Creasy does.

835
01:37:03.511 --> 01:37:08.574
He'll deliver more justice in a weekend
than 10 years of your courts and tribunals.

836
01:37:08.683 --> 01:37:12.016
- Just stay out of his way.
- I plan to.

837
01:37:19.461 --> 01:37:22.919
I will even help him. if I can.

838
01:37:23.031 --> 01:37:27.195
But. uh. I would like to
understand him.

839
01:37:29.037 --> 01:37:30.699
Give me that.

840
01:37:30.807 --> 01:37:33.435
Pita Ramos...

841
01:37:35.011 --> 01:37:36.911
that's a number to you.

842
01:37:37.013 --> 01:37:41.950
You know. one more dead.
but a number.

843
01:37:42.051 --> 01:37:44.645
What was she to Creasy then?

844
01:37:44.754 --> 01:37:47.587
She showed him
it was all right to live again.

845
01:37:50.728 --> 01:37:54.789
And the kidnappers
took that away. huh?

846
01:37:54.899 --> 01:37:58.858
And they're gonna wish
they never touched a hair on her head.

847
01:38:00.437 --> 01:38:03.634
A man can be an artist...

848
01:38:06.543 --> 01:38:09.172
in anything... food. whatever.

849
01:38:09.281 --> 01:38:13.843
It depends on how good he is at it.

850
01:38:17.255 --> 01:38:19.155
Creasy's art is death.

851
01:38:22.027 --> 01:38:25.828
He's about to paint his masterpiece.

852
01:38:33.205 --> 01:38:35.673
I don't have anything else to say.

853
01:40:04.301 --> 01:40:06.929
Shh. Shh.

854
01:40:25.490 --> 01:40:27.822
Forgiveness is between them and God.

855
01:40:27.926 --> 01:40:30.827
It's my job to arrange the meeting.

856
01:42:27.186 --> 01:42:29.916
Don't move.
Put your hands down. Put 'em down.

857
01:42:38.631 --> 01:42:41.259
<i>Señor John W. Creasy...</i>

858
01:42:41.367 --> 01:42:44.859
<i>is under arrest for the murder
of two officers of the Judicial Police.</i>

859
01:42:46.973 --> 01:42:50.067
<i>He's suspected
of possible involvement...</i>

860
01:42:50.176 --> 01:42:53.634
<i>of possible involvement in
the kidnapping of Lupita Ramos.</i>

861
01:43:23.645 --> 01:43:26.443
Can you hear me? Huh?

862
01:43:28.083 --> 01:43:30.051
Know where we are?

863
01:43:31.286 --> 01:43:35.656
We're under the bridge
where the deal went bad.

864
01:43:35.758 --> 01:43:40.525
The ransom got stolen.
You wanna tell me what happened?

865
01:43:40.630 --> 01:43:43.292
<i>- Have you heard of La Hermandad?
- Yes. I have.</i>

866
01:43:43.399 --> 01:43:45.299
<i>- Do you know what it is?
- Yes.</i>

867
01:43:45.401 --> 01:43:47.528
<i>I'm the president of La Hermandad.</i>

868
01:43:47.637 --> 01:43:49.332
- You're the president?
- Yes.

869
01:43:49.438 --> 01:43:51.532
<i>The president? Wow.</i>

870
01:43:51.642 --> 01:43:53.701
Look at me.

871
01:43:54.978 --> 01:43:57.378
Oh. you can't.
I'm sorry.

872
01:43:57.481 --> 01:43:59.540
How's that?

873
01:44:08.091 --> 01:44:10.060
Let me show you what I got here.

874
01:44:11.996 --> 01:44:15.523
See this? This is a charger. It's used
by convicts to hide money and drugs.

875
01:44:15.633 --> 01:44:19.330
They stick it in their body.
They tuck it up their rectum.

876
01:44:19.437 --> 01:44:22.668
You familiar with that?
This... Look at me.

877
01:44:22.774 --> 01:44:25.538
Pencil detonator.

878
01:44:25.643 --> 01:44:29.375
Timer. used as a receiver-transmitter.

879
01:44:29.481 --> 01:44:32.507
C-4. Highly explosive.

880
01:44:32.618 --> 01:44:34.848
You put 'em all together.
you got a bomb.

881
01:44:34.953 --> 01:44:37.513
Not very sophisticated.
but very powerful.

882
01:44:39.725 --> 01:44:42.353
That's what you have in your ass right now.

883
01:44:42.461 --> 01:44:45.829
Don't move. Don't move.
Don't move.

884
01:44:50.103 --> 01:44:52.571
Cheap watch. Pager watch.

885
01:44:52.672 --> 01:44:58.304
Used to send a page to the receiver
that's up your behind right now.

886
01:44:58.411 --> 01:45:01.608
<i>So. I'm gonna send you a page...</i>

887
01:45:01.715 --> 01:45:03.616
which you will receive...

888
01:45:06.787 --> 01:45:09.278
in five minutes.

889
01:45:09.390 --> 01:45:11.620
Now.

890
01:45:16.464 --> 01:45:18.864
You got less than five minutes
to tell me what went down...

891
01:45:18.966 --> 01:45:22.095
between your men and the kidnapper.

892
01:45:22.204 --> 01:45:24.035
I have nothing to do with the kidnapper.

893
01:45:24.139 --> 01:45:26.767
- Four minutes and 30 seconds.
- Nothing. I don't know him.

894
01:45:26.875 --> 01:45:30.572
<i>You don't know?
Four minutes and 25 seconds.</i>

895
01:45:32.714 --> 01:45:34.705
Four minutes and 20 seconds.
Are you sure?

896
01:45:37.552 --> 01:45:40.420
Okay.

897
01:45:40.523 --> 01:45:43.754
I got all the time in the world.
You don't. but I do.

898
01:45:43.860 --> 01:45:46.624
- Hey. relax. relax. buddy.
- I'm relaxed.

899
01:45:46.729 --> 01:45:49.596
You got three minutes. 59 seconds.

900
01:45:49.699 --> 01:45:52.463
I saw the opportunity.
and I got lucky.

901
01:45:52.568 --> 01:45:54.058
And?

902
01:45:54.170 --> 01:45:57.265
And I had my men ready as we
got instructions where to go.

903
01:45:57.374 --> 01:45:59.308
You had your men ready
to steal the drop.

904
01:45:59.410 --> 01:46:01.844
<i>You had your men ready to kill
one of the kidnappers. yeah?</i>

905
01:46:01.945 --> 01:46:04.470
<i>You've done this many times.</i>

906
01:46:06.383 --> 01:46:09.682
- One of the nephews of the head kidnapper...
- Bingo. Bingo. Bingo.

907
01:46:09.787 --> 01:46:12.847
- Bingo. yeah. You've done this many times. huh?
- Many times. yeah.

908
01:46:12.956 --> 01:46:16.290
- Yeah. Killed many victims too. haven't you?
- Come on. sir.

909
01:46:16.394 --> 01:46:19.363
- We just make out as best we can.
- "As best we could"?

910
01:46:22.434 --> 01:46:25.528
Two minutes. 47 seconds.

911
01:46:27.005 --> 01:46:30.270
Wait-Wait a minute. Come on.

912
01:46:30.375 --> 01:46:32.639
<i>- I have a little gift for you.
- For me?</i>

913
01:46:32.744 --> 01:46:35.543
- Yeah. Come on. Come on.
- What do you got?

914
01:46:35.648 --> 01:46:39.778
<i>There was no $10 million.
There was one half in the bags.</i>

915
01:46:39.885 --> 01:46:42.615
The ransom was $10 million?
They put it in two bags.

916
01:46:42.721 --> 01:46:44.848
- Five million in each bag. right?
- Two bags. true.

917
01:46:44.957 --> 01:46:48.484
<i>But one has half paper...</i>

918
01:46:48.594 --> 01:46:51.689
<i>the other only paper.</i>

919
01:46:51.798 --> 01:46:55.700
Maybe your men stole it.

920
01:46:55.802 --> 01:46:58.293
Whoever did it
took it before the exchange.

921
01:47:00.340 --> 01:47:03.309
Okay. At the Ramos house...

922
01:47:03.410 --> 01:47:08.040
before the exchange.
who put the bags in the car?

923
01:47:08.148 --> 01:47:10.413
- Guess what.
- What?

924
01:47:10.518 --> 01:47:13.817
Ramos lawyer. Jordan Kalfus.

925
01:47:13.921 --> 01:47:16.389
- Jordan Kalfus?
- Yeah.

926
01:47:19.026 --> 01:47:21.494
Pedro.

927
01:47:28.770 --> 01:47:31.261
Sir? Please.

928
01:47:31.373 --> 01:47:34.069
I- I'm sorry.
I'm really sorry for the girl.

929
01:47:34.176 --> 01:47:38.169
It was just business.
You know. I'm a professional.

930
01:47:38.280 --> 01:47:41.579
That's what everybody keeps saying.
"I'm just a professional. "

931
01:47:41.683 --> 01:47:44.481
Everybody keeps saying that to me.
"I'm just a professional. I'm just a professional. "

932
01:47:44.586 --> 01:47:47.613
I'm getting sick and tired of hearing that.
You understand me?

933
01:47:51.027 --> 01:47:53.962
What are you going to do now?

934
01:47:54.063 --> 01:47:56.190
What am I gonna do?
I'm gonna leave. I gotta go.

935
01:47:56.299 --> 01:47:59.462
- Yeah. I got...
- Come on. Come on. What about me. huh?

936
01:47:59.569 --> 01:48:02.538
- What about you? You got 40 seconds.
- Come on.

937
01:48:02.639 --> 01:48:07.077
- Thirty-five.
- A last wish. please. Please.

938
01:48:07.177 --> 01:48:12.410
Last wish?
I wish you had more time.

939
01:48:12.516 --> 01:48:16.612
Hey! Hey. hey!

940
01:50:19.116 --> 01:50:22.745
Hola.

941
01:50:22.853 --> 01:50:25.481
<i>- Mariana. it's me.
- Creasy. where are you?</i>

942
01:50:25.589 --> 01:50:28.252
Listen. I got something
that looks like banking codes...

943
01:50:28.360 --> 01:50:30.225
from Bank Coast in the Cayman Islands.

944
01:50:30.328 --> 01:50:33.456
- I need it translated as fast as you can.
- Whose account is it?

945
01:50:33.565 --> 01:50:37.661
<i>Jordan Kalfus. and it looks like
U.S. Deposits and withdrawals.</i>

946
01:50:37.769 --> 01:50:39.703
<i>Give me the same thing
on Samuel Ramos.</i>

947
01:50:39.805 --> 01:50:43.536
Samuel Ramos. That's it?

948
01:50:43.642 --> 01:50:45.371
- That's it.
- Okay.

949
01:51:20.614 --> 01:51:22.515
<i>Gracias.</i>

950
01:51:30.959 --> 01:51:34.588
- Creasy.
- Samuel.

951
01:51:34.696 --> 01:51:36.687
<i>Honey?</i>

952
01:51:40.301 --> 01:51:42.668
What's going on?

953
01:51:44.473 --> 01:51:48.500
That's what I wanna know.
What is going on?

954
01:51:50.946 --> 01:51:53.847
<i>Huh. Sam?</i>

955
01:51:53.949 --> 01:51:56.179
I'm gonna ask your wife a couple
of questions. okay?

956
01:51:56.285 --> 01:51:59.221
You move...

957
01:51:59.322 --> 01:52:01.347
<i>you make one sound...</i>

958
01:52:01.458 --> 01:52:04.552
I'll snatch the life right outta you.
you understand?

959
01:52:11.868 --> 01:52:14.564
What happened. Lisa. hmm?

960
01:52:14.671 --> 01:52:16.571
Were you in on this?

961
01:52:16.674 --> 01:52:20.838
- Or was it just your husband. huh?
- Am I in on what?

962
01:52:20.945 --> 01:52:24.472
You know what I'm talking about... Pita's
kidnapping. her death. Were you a part of it?

963
01:52:24.582 --> 01:52:27.881
- Pita got killed because the ransom got stolen.
- Shut up!

964
01:52:29.420 --> 01:52:31.786
Yeah. the money was stolen.
You're right. He's right.

965
01:52:31.889 --> 01:52:35.417
The money was stolen by Victor Fuentes.
How much was stolen though. huh?

966
01:52:35.527 --> 01:52:38.519
- $2.5 million. right?
- What are you talking about?

967
01:52:38.630 --> 01:52:41.758
He knows what I'm talking about.
$2.5 million. That's what Victor got. isn't it?

968
01:52:41.867 --> 01:52:44.859
- What are you talking about?
- 2.5 million.

969
01:52:44.970 --> 01:52:47.268
<i>2.5 million to your lawyer
Jordan Kalfus...</i>

970
01:52:47.372 --> 01:52:50.500
that he put in an account in the Cayman
Islands. but he won't get a chance to spend it.

971
01:52:53.847 --> 01:52:56.179
What happened to the other five. Sam?

972
01:52:56.282 --> 01:52:59.217
<i>Huh? That's 2.5. 2.5.
What is five from 10?</i>

973
01:52:59.319 --> 01:53:01.844
That's five. What happened
to the other five. Sam? Tell your wife.

974
01:53:01.955 --> 01:53:04.389
<i>- It's your chance to talk.
What happened to the other five?</i>

975
01:53:04.490 --> 01:53:05.855
- You got a wife. Creasy?
- No. I don't have a wife.

976
01:53:05.959 --> 01:53:08.723
Then you'll never know how hard
it could be to tell your wife the truth.

977
01:53:08.828 --> 01:53:11.059
No. you have a wife!
You tell me what happened!

978
01:53:11.165 --> 01:53:13.292
It was in this room
that my father prayed.

979
01:53:13.400 --> 01:53:16.096
- I don't give a fuck about your fucking father!
- My father prayed.

980
01:53:16.203 --> 01:53:20.105
He prayed that his gambling debts and his
infidelities would be forgiven right in this room.

981
01:53:20.207 --> 01:53:22.903
- Samuel! I love you!
- What. Lisa?

982
01:53:23.010 --> 01:53:26.810
- Tell me the truth.
- I didn't inherit a kingdom! That's the truth!

983
01:53:26.914 --> 01:53:29.816
You wanna know the truth?
I inherited his debt and his mess.

984
01:53:29.918 --> 01:53:32.819
- I inherited his lawyer Jordan...
- You tell me what happened to my baby!

985
01:53:32.921 --> 01:53:35.481
Say it! Say it! Say it!

986
01:53:35.590 --> 01:53:38.218
Say it! Say it! Be a fucking man!

987
01:53:42.030 --> 01:53:44.464
Jordan told me she'd sit in a room...

988
01:53:44.566 --> 01:53:46.966
and watch cartoons all day...

989
01:53:47.069 --> 01:53:49.936
and she'd eat ice cream
and we'd have her back in two days.

990
01:53:50.039 --> 01:53:52.633
He lied to me!

991
01:53:52.742 --> 01:53:55.609
That's why he's fucking dead!
I did it!

992
01:53:55.711 --> 01:53:57.770
I did it. Lisa!

993
01:53:57.880 --> 01:54:00.610
I agreed to the kidnapping.

994
01:54:00.716 --> 01:54:04.152
I did it for us...
for the three of us.

995
01:54:12.596 --> 01:54:14.723
I'm so sorry. Lisa.

996
01:54:20.737 --> 01:54:22.705
You kill him.

997
01:54:24.108 --> 01:54:26.008
You kill him or I will.

998
01:54:56.375 --> 01:54:58.343
Huh. You know. they say a. um...

999
01:55:00.747 --> 01:55:03.875
<i>a bullet always tells the truth.</i>

1000
01:55:13.159 --> 01:55:15.127
It never lies.

1001
01:55:28.109 --> 01:55:32.375
It didn't work for me. Samuel. but maybe...

1002
01:55:34.648 --> 01:55:37.209
Maybe it'll work for you.

1003
01:55:46.528 --> 01:55:49.122
<i>I'll pray for you.</i>

1004
01:58:51.590 --> 01:58:53.490
<i>Gracias.</i>

1005
01:59:18.285 --> 01:59:20.185
- ¿Hola?
- Hola.

1006
01:59:20.287 --> 01:59:22.778
<i>- Mr. Creasy?
- Yeah. it's me.</i>

1007
01:59:22.889 --> 01:59:24.950
<i>I traced the PIN for you
and I have an address.</i>

1008
01:59:26.051 --> 01:59:27.051
<i>Yeah?</i>

1009
01:59:27.060 --> 01:59:30.518
<i>The cardholder is Reina Rosas Sanchez.
the wife of The Voice. "</i>

1010
01:59:30.632 --> 01:59:34.898
<i>She lives in Los Arcos.
apartment 26D. Via Appia.</i>

1011
01:59:35.003 --> 01:59:37.471
<i>- Good.
- And another thing.</i>

1012
01:59:37.572 --> 01:59:41.372
<i>Pick up today's paper and you'll have
a picture of The Voice. "</i>

1013
01:59:41.476 --> 01:59:43.444
<i>Good. Thank you.</i>

1014
02:00:46.445 --> 02:00:48.538
Shh. shh. shh.

1015
02:01:52.013 --> 02:01:53.947
<i>José? ¿Qué te pasa?</i>

1016
02:03:09.028 --> 02:03:10.859
<i>Sí.</i>

1017
02:03:10.964 --> 02:03:12.932
Okay.

1018
02:03:20.507 --> 02:03:22.270
Hmm?

1019
02:03:28.782 --> 02:03:30.249
Hmm?

1020
02:03:41.362 --> 02:03:43.262
<i>Sí.</i>

1021
02:03:43.364 --> 02:03:45.356
Okay. Uh...

1022
02:03:49.704 --> 02:03:51.604
<i>- ¿Sí?
- Sí.</i>

1023
02:03:58.813 --> 02:04:01.441
Aurelio Rosas Sanchez. Okay.

1024
02:04:06.322 --> 02:04:08.222
Okay.

1025
02:04:16.666 --> 02:04:18.600
<i>Sí.</i>

1026
02:04:18.701 --> 02:04:21.102
<i>Sí.</i>

1027
02:04:21.204 --> 02:04:23.138
Huh?

1028
02:05:20.000 --> 02:05:21.968
<i>Momento.</i>

1029
02:05:51.633 --> 02:05:53.567
<i>Hola. Daniel.</i>

1030
02:05:53.669 --> 02:05:55.534
Señor Creasy.

1031
02:05:55.637 --> 02:05:59.004
Yeah. Yeah. I got your family here.

1032
02:05:59.107 --> 02:06:01.667
<i>Your brother doesn't look too good.</i>

1033
02:06:01.777 --> 02:06:05.042
<i>Yeah. Reina. she's what.
about eight months?</i>

1034
02:06:05.147 --> 02:06:09.209
<i>Huh? You wanna negotiate?</i>

1035
02:06:13.122 --> 02:06:16.785
The most important thing
in life is family.

1036
02:06:16.893 --> 02:06:19.088
<i>Do you agree?</i>

1037
02:06:20.296 --> 02:06:22.196
I agree.

1038
02:06:24.000 --> 02:06:26.469
And there you are.
You have my family.

1039
02:06:26.570 --> 02:06:29.437
Well. most of my family.

1040
02:06:29.540 --> 02:06:33.704
<i>My wife and I are separated.
You know how that is.</i>

1041
02:06:33.811 --> 02:06:37.577
Now. tell me seriously.
h- how much do you want?

1042
02:06:37.681 --> 02:06:39.444
Ah.

1043
02:06:41.985 --> 02:06:44.477
Your brother wants to speak to you.
Yeah. hold on.

1044
02:06:55.567 --> 02:06:58.730
I'm gonna take your family apart
piece by piece. You understand me?

1045
02:06:58.837 --> 02:07:00.896
Piece by piece. Shut up!

1046
02:07:02.107 --> 02:07:04.906
<i>I don't want your money!</i>

1047
02:07:05.010 --> 02:07:08.639
Do you understand me?
You understand me? I want you.

1048
02:07:41.783 --> 02:07:43.876
I'm listening.

1049
02:07:45.319 --> 02:07:48.686
<i>I'm listening. Daniel. I'm listening.</i>

1050
02:07:54.896 --> 02:07:58.196
<i>All right.
I will give you a life for a life.</i>

1051
02:07:59.802 --> 02:08:02.362
Whose life?
What are you talking about?

1052
02:08:02.471 --> 02:08:05.235
<i>Whose life. Daniel? I want you.</i>

1053
02:08:05.340 --> 02:08:08.832
I will give you her life for your life.

1054
02:08:08.944 --> 02:08:13.404
And in exchange.
I will get my life back.

1055
02:08:13.515 --> 02:08:17.509
- What life? Whose life?
- The girl's. Pita's.

1056
02:08:21.424 --> 02:08:25.588
- Pita's dead.
- Creasy!

1057
02:08:25.695 --> 02:08:31.031
<i>I'm a businessman.
A girl dead is worth nothing. She's alive.</i>

1058
02:08:35.339 --> 02:08:37.307
All right.

1059
02:08:39.243 --> 02:08:41.438
I want proof of life. You hear me?

1060
02:08:41.545 --> 02:08:44.514
I want proof of life.
I want... I want...

1061
02:08:44.615 --> 02:08:47.049
I want the name of her bear.
What does she call her bear?

1062
02:08:47.151 --> 02:08:49.779
<i>You tell her to tell you...</i>

1063
02:08:49.887 --> 02:08:53.415
to tell me what she calls her bear.

1064
02:09:22.221 --> 02:09:24.815
- Yeah?
- Creasy.

1065
02:09:24.924 --> 02:09:27.917
<i>She calls the bear Creasy Bear.</i>

1066
02:09:43.844 --> 02:09:45.813
Okay.

1067
02:09:47.649 --> 02:09:50.243
O- Okay.

1068
02:09:50.351 --> 02:09:52.911
I give you your brother.
you give me the girl.

1069
02:09:54.656 --> 02:09:56.988
- All right.
- Where?

1070
02:10:40.671 --> 02:10:42.571
Hello?

1071
02:10:42.673 --> 02:10:45.335
Lisa. listen to me. Don't hang up.

1072
02:10:45.443 --> 02:10:47.638
I think Pita's alive.

1073
02:10:49.447 --> 02:10:51.677
I can't take this anymore.

1074
02:10:51.782 --> 02:10:53.716
Take the road to Puebla.

1075
02:10:53.818 --> 02:10:56.685
Get off junction 34. south side.

1076
02:10:56.787 --> 02:10:58.813
I'll meet you there in two hours.

1077
02:11:44.138 --> 02:11:46.038
So where is she?

1078
02:11:48.575 --> 02:11:51.703
She's right over there.
You see those two cars out there?

1079
02:11:57.018 --> 02:12:00.283
Pita's kidnapper. Daniel...

1080
02:12:00.388 --> 02:12:03.721
this is his brother.

1081
02:12:05.093 --> 02:12:07.220
Here.

1082
02:12:07.328 --> 02:12:11.060
I'm goin' up on the bridge to get Pita.

1083
02:12:11.167 --> 02:12:13.931
<i>If anything goes wrong.
you put it to his head.</i>

1084
02:12:15.504 --> 02:12:17.631
You pull the trigger. all right?

1085
02:12:18.674 --> 02:12:21.199
You understand?

1086
02:12:24.280 --> 02:12:26.646
You don't...

1087
02:12:26.749 --> 02:12:30.015
Let him loose until she's with you.

1088
02:12:30.120 --> 02:12:32.088
You got it?

1089
02:12:34.558 --> 02:12:37.220
And you don't wait for me. okay?

1090
02:12:39.963 --> 02:12:41.692
Yeah.

1091
02:12:41.798 --> 02:12:45.359
- You'll be all right. You okay?
- Yeah.

1092
02:14:30.546 --> 02:14:32.446
Creasy!

1093
02:14:34.217 --> 02:14:36.186
Creasy!

1094
02:14:37.354 --> 02:14:39.822
Creasy!

1095
02:14:56.107 --> 02:14:58.507
- You all right?
- Yeah.

1096
02:14:58.610 --> 02:15:01.306
They didn't hurt you?

1097
02:15:01.412 --> 02:15:03.744
Hi.

1098
02:15:06.484 --> 02:15:10.785
Your mother's waitin' for you. She's right
down there at the end of the bridge.

1099
02:15:10.889 --> 02:15:14.518
- Okay? You go home.
- Okay.

1100
02:15:14.627 --> 02:15:17.357
- All right.
- Where are you goin'?

1101
02:15:21.233 --> 02:15:23.701
I'm goin' home too.

1102
02:15:24.737 --> 02:15:26.637
I'm goin' to Blue Bayou.

1103
02:15:30.910 --> 02:15:33.538
Oh. Hey.

1104
02:15:33.647 --> 02:15:36.980
I got something for you.

1105
02:15:39.052 --> 02:15:41.043
I got the last number too.

1106
02:15:41.154 --> 02:15:43.987
I love you. Creasy.

1107
02:15:46.493 --> 02:15:49.156
And you love me. don't you?

1108
02:15:50.264 --> 02:15:52.357
Yes. I do.

1109
02:15:52.466 --> 02:15:55.663
With all my heart. Pita. go.

1110
02:15:55.770 --> 02:15:57.738
- Go. Run.
- Bye.

1111
02:16:11.286 --> 02:16:13.186
<i>¡Vamos!</i>

1112
02:16:13.288 --> 02:16:16.553
- Pita! Baby. come here. It's okay.
- Mom!

1113
02:16:16.658 --> 02:16:19.855
<i>- Mom!
- Come on! Okay. I'll let you go now.</i>

1114
02:16:19.961 --> 02:16:22.020
<i>Mom!</i>
